1 Rock et Engine Testing Development Grant Program to offer financial
2 assistance by grant to private or public entities for the purpose of
3 expanding the aircraft or rocket engine testing capabilities of this
4 state and developing aircraft or rocket engine testing
5 infrastructure. Grant funding shall be administered based on the
6 potential for a specific project to enhance the aviation, and
7 aerospace, and space propulsion industry of this state. A grant
8 under this program shall be a one-time award.
9 B. Public, private, and nonprofit entities within this state
10 that have sufficient financial and management capacity to complete
11 the requested project are eligible for funding under this program.
12 Applicants shall provide the following information:
13 1. Airline or industry support as evidenced by a letter or
14 other communication directly from the entity stating its support for
15 the project;
16 2. The ability to provide a minimum of forty percent (40%)
17 matching funds for the project; and
18 3. A proposal summary that shall include any background
19 information or history with aircraft or rocket engine testing and
20 development, project description, timeline for completion of
21 project, and estimated budget for the entire project.
22 C. A grant agreement shall be made between any awardee and the
23 Department. The grant agreement shall provide for the conditions of
24 disbursement, shall include a provision requiring the repayment of
