1 awar ded funds if the terms are not met, and shall include a
2 requirement for awardees to provide ongoing quarterly reports
3 detailing activity related to the project.
4 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY Section 3, Chapter 125, O.S.L.
5 2024 (3 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 503), is amended to read as
6 follows:
7 Section 503. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a
8 revolving fund for the Oklahoma Department of Aerospace and
9 Aeronautics to be designated the “Oklahoma Aircraft and Rocket
10 Engine Testing Development Grant Program Revolving Fund”. The fund
11 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
12 and shall consist of all monies received by the Department from all
13 monies received by any public or private donations, contributions,
14 and gifts received for the benefit of the fund, and any amounts
15 appropriated by the Legislature, provided for the purpose of funding
16 grants as provided in this act the Oklahoma Aircraft and Rocket
17 Engine Testing Development Grant Program. All monies accruing to
18 the credit of the fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted
19 and expended by the Department for the purpose provided for in this
20 act the Oklahoma Aircraft and Rocket Engine Testing Development
21 Grant Program. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon
22 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
23 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
24 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
